    <item>
      <title>Re: Everquest's fundamental growth problem</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=SOE&amp;message.id=4762#M4762</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;EQs gradually declining numbers are really easy to explain.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;#1 - The world is simply too big.&lt;BR&gt;When many of us began, there were just Odus, Antonica and Faydwer.&amp;nbsp; If you were level 1-10ish you were already where you should be when you started.&amp;nbsp; After that you started having a few choices, but the choices were limited enough that you could be assured there were others of your level range there hunting to group with.&lt;BR&gt;Unfortunately, while new content can be fun and interesting, having new zones added every few months introduces a serious group problem, primarily for lower level characters.&amp;nbsp; As there were more and more places to be, there were fewer and fewer at any given one of them.&amp;nbsp; Finding a group became such a problem they added the LFG tools (which new players don't know how to use even after the tutorial) and even with PoK books finding these zones is difficult for anyone who wasn't around before PoP.&amp;nbsp; And any actual "New" player's characters are likely to be seriously undergeared relative to the Alts they're grouping with.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;#2 - SoE loves raiders.&lt;BR&gt;I don't have a problem with raiding, I have been through the gamut of it.&amp;nbsp; From pre-Kunark pickups on fear and hate, to small guild raids on kael during velius, to medium and eventually high end raiding in anguish.&lt;BR&gt;Unfortunately, each successive expansion (with some exception) has been targetted primarily on the higher end/raid guild content.&lt;BR&gt;LDoN was a wonderful concept, but the exp nerf destroyed it.&lt;BR&gt;DoN missions were a nice try, but since nobody wants to group with anyone under 70, and expects raid-obtained gear and tons of AAS.. well high end wins again.&lt;BR&gt;DoDH introducing MMs was a miracle, but because people were using them to PL alts SoE decided to throw all of the time and resources they invested in that concept down the toilet instead of simply restricting MMs to giving AA exp and not Level exp.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;#3 - SoE likes locks.&lt;BR&gt;This is probably the single largest contributing factor to players quitting after 50.&lt;BR&gt;Imagine if you made a character today....&lt;BR&gt;Do you honestly believe that even with the help of your better friends in the game, that this new character will ever finish PoP, DoN and DoDH progressions?&amp;nbsp; Will they ever even see KT?&lt;BR&gt;How many years have you played to accumulate those friends who might help you?&lt;BR&gt;New players start discovering these barriers in their 50s and quickly learn that their chances of getting keyed or flagged for most of them are long since past, as the numbers required to accomplish the keyings are already past them and on to new content.&lt;BR&gt;Being told that you "have no chance to" anything is bad.&amp;nbsp; While it is not entirely factual, it is, for most practical purposes, true.&amp;nbsp; Guilds don't go around collecting up new players and helping them get their PoP flags or to kill DoN dragons.&amp;nbsp; They have already done that and are off to do something else.&lt;BR&gt;I suspect that within a year's time, even finding a group to work on signets for Anguish will be a thing of the past.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;SoE needs to seriously re-evaluate the direction they're taking EQ if they wish it to last.&amp;nbsp; The high-end players will be harder and harder to please as time goes on, and the gap seperating them from everyone else continues to grow.&amp;nbsp; As they leave, they are not being replaced, because the power to accomplish the needed steps to BE one of them is becomming more and more difficult to obtain (read: numbers of willing players).&lt;BR&gt;As they continue to design more and more based on a diminishing portion of the player base, they continue to alienate the potential next generations, and further shorten the life of the game.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Monster Missions were the single best solution to a lot of the problems.&amp;nbsp; But thanks to a rush to fix an oversight, they have pushed them out of popularity to the point that finding a group for any but the newest (dains) is next to impossible.&lt;BR&gt;-They nerfed the exp on most of them to reduce the exp farmability factor.. okay that makes sense.&lt;BR&gt;-They increased the difficulty on most of them to reduce the exp farmability facotr ... Ummm.. wasn't that why the exp was reduced?&lt;BR&gt;-They make the 45 minute lockout global to Eliminate the farmability factor...&amp;nbsp;:smileywink: . Can we have the old exp and difficilties back now?&lt;/P&gt;</description>
