      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I beleive that TSS can be the savior of EQ if it will bring in new blood. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;However, this drive to have it DD only will NOT attract new players, well very few anyway. There appears to be an almost total lack of interest in marketing EQ. The was another comment a couple of weeks ago (I forget which thread) saying it wouold be advertised in some obscure magazine only available in the US. So, with little to no coverage in advertising, no chance of seeing the game appear in any gaming shop, until after xmas according to the boards and even then probably only in the US I just cannot comprehend how any right minded marketing person can consider that any strategy is in place to attract this new blood.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;It is only this new blood that will help EQ grow. The old and bold members on here will continue to dwindle, server mergers will probably happen again and eventually the gamer will die. I do not want this to happen but why should the onus on providing customers for a commercail profit making company have to rely on word of mouth from its existing customer base. Are they going to pay me, or credit me subscription time, for every new player I bring to the game?? DONT think so !!!&lt;/P&gt;</description>
