      <description>There are a lot of reasons Everquest has a shrinking userbase.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&amp;nbsp;(1) Bugs. Way too many bugs. SoE pushes out content too fast to do a good job of debugging it first.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&amp;nbsp;(2) This might seem strange, but TOO MUCH content. Even high end&#xD;
raid guilds complain that expansions come out too often - and MOST&#xD;
players will take years to see all the content in any given new&#xD;
expansion, if they ever get the chance to see it at all. ONE expansion&#xD;
a year would be a lot better, and would help address point 1.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&amp;nbsp;(3) TOO much graphics. When I zone into an empty New Freeport and&#xD;
get more lag than I ever saw in the Bazaar, there is something WRONG&#xD;
with the graphics content level. This is one of the things that killed&#xD;
EQ2 - pretty graphics at the EXPENCE of good gameplay.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&amp;nbsp;(4) Did I mention bugs?&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&amp;nbsp;(5) Pathetic customer support. When *I* knew more about the game&#xD;
3 months in than a so-called "Game MASTER" knows, there's something&#xD;
wrong with that Game Master - either in training or experience. IMO SoE&#xD;
should be recruiting their Game Masters and a lot of their other&#xD;
customer support from their existing Guides, they might get folks that&#xD;
have a clue that way.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&amp;nbsp;(6) Quests that are worthless or have a reward that is NOT in&#xD;
balance with the benefit. The way things are right now, World of&#xD;
Warcraft has a far better claim to the name "EverQUEST" than EQ does -&#xD;
quests in WoW tend to be balanced on the difficulty to reward a LOT&#xD;
better than EQ quests are.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&amp;nbsp;(7) Creaping featuritis. I hated what I saw of the EQ2 interface&#xD;
when it was in EQ - WHY is SoE trying to inflict that overfancy hunk of&#xD;
junk on EQ of late? The "Old Default" interface is a LOT better&#xD;
interface than that EQ2 piece of junk.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&amp;nbsp;SoE seems disenclined to learn from it's competition - they have&#xD;
constantly blown off suggestions that they at least TRY to match the&#xD;
factors from other games that make those games ENJOYABLE. They seem to&#xD;
have gotten the impression that "pretty graphics make the game better",&#xD;
and have NOT learned from the EQ2 fiasco that "overfancy graphics make&#xD;
the game a PITA and the player experiance WORSE".&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&amp;nbsp;I also get the impression that SoE never really had a good handle on why EQ became popular in the first place.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
